<p>If you teach in an Indian school or college, you've probably heard about ChatGPT and AI from your students, your principal, or social media. But the real question isn't whether AI is interesting; it's whether these tools save you time on the work you actually do, lesson planning, grading, parent emails, and creating worksheets, and whether they're worth a monthly subscription on a teacher's budget.</p>

<p>This guide is the practical answer for Indian teachers in 2026.</p>

<h2>Why teachers should care about AI tools</h2>

<p>Most Indian schools have not bought AI subscriptions for staff. That means whatever you use, you are paying for. The good news: the most useful AI tool for the bulk of teaching work is the free version of Claude. Many Indian teachers run their entire week on it without paying anything.</p>

