<h2>How to pay for AI tools as an Indian teacher</h2>

<p>Indian debit cards are often rejected by international AI services. The most reliable methods for teachers: a <strong>forex card</strong> from HDFC or Axis (one-time setup, predictable INR cost), or <strong>Niyo Global</strong> (low forex markup, near-instant approval). Read the full payment guide: <a href="/guides/pay-for-ai-tools-india/">5 ways to pay for AI tools from India</a>.</p>

<p>Canva Pro bills you in INR directly, so your normal Indian card works.</p>

<h2>Common questions from Indian teachers</h2>

<h3>Will my school find out I am using AI?</h3>
<p>Only if you copy AI output verbatim into student-facing materials with errors. AI-generated lesson plans are widely accepted as productivity tools; AI-written student feedback is a grey area, use it as a draft you edit.</p>

<h3>Are these tools safe for student data?</h3>
<p>Claude's privacy default (no training on your chats) is the strongest of the three. Avoid pasting full student names or roll numbers into any AI tool, just first names or anonymised IDs.</p>

